Sure, here are some examples of how to use the word "baze" in different forms and positions in Serbian:

1. *Baze* su ključne za uspeh u biznisu. (Nouns, subject position) 
(English: Bases are key to success in business.)

2. Ove *baze* podataka su veoma korisne. (Nouns, object position)
(English: These databases are very useful.)

3. Nismo sigurni da li će nova *baza* biti uspostavljena. (Noun, subject position)
(English: We're not sure if the new base will be established.)

4. Proučavam različite *baze* podataka kako bih pronašao najbolju za svoj projekat. (Nouns, object position)
(English: I'm studying different databases to find the best one for my project.)

5. Danas smo dodali nove *baze* podataka u sistem. (Nouns, object position)
(English: Today we added new databases to the system.)

6. Izolacija je proces razdvajanja *baznih* jedinjenja. (Adjective, prenominal position)
(English: Isolation is the process of separating basic compounds.)

7. *Bazno* reagovanje je jedno od najosnovnijih hemijskih procesa. (Adjective, postnominal position)
(English: Basic reaction is one of the most fundamental chemical processes.)

8. Moramo prilagoditi strategiju prema *bazama* naših klijenata. (Nouns, genitive case)
(English: We need to adjust our strategy according to our clients' bases.)

9. U laboratoriji sam radio sa *bazama* i kiselinama. (Nouns, instrumental case)
(English: In the laboratory, I worked with bases and acids.)

10. *Bazična* reakcija je započela nakon dodavanja kalcijum-hidroksida. (Adjective, prenominal position)
(English: Basic reaction started after adding calcium hydroxide.)

Note: Please note that the translations may not be word-for-word but convey the same meaning as the original sentences.